comment: This reminds me of two YouTubers whom I like because they cover a lot of good subjects, but one almost always uses blatant  strawman arguments, and the other one wildly misinterprets the information he presents - he once cited the first half of an article in which the early results of a scientific study seemed to support his bias, but he disregarded the rest of the article which showed that the long term results of the study completely refuted his bias. The first one seems deliberately disingenuous while the other seems sincere but unable to separate the evidence from what he wants to believe. They each have a little over five times as many subscribers as you, and I often agree with them on an emotional level, but I think you do a much better job of giving the facts in a fair and accurate way even when they're different from what you would like them to be. This is why I'm subscribed to you.
